<h2>Octave 4.0 has been Released</h2>
<p>
Octave 4.0.0 is now available
at <a href="ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/octave/octave-4.0.0.tar.xz">ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/octave/octave-4.0.0.tar.xz</a>.
</p>
<p>
Octave 4.0 is a major new release with many new features, including a
graphical user interface, support for classdef object-oriented
programming, better compatibility with Matlab, and many new and
improved functions.
</p>
<p>
An official Windows binary installer is also available
from <a href="ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/octave/windows/octave-4.0.0_0-installer.exe">ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/octave/windows/octave-4.0.0_0-installer.exe</a>
</p>
<p>
A list of important user-visible changes is availble
at <a href="http://octave.org/NEWS.html">http://octave.org/NEWS.html</a>,
by selecting the Release Notes item in the News menu of the GUI, or by
typing <tt>news</tt> at the Octave command prompt.
</p>
<p>
Thanks to the many people who contributed to this release!
</p>
<p>
<small><em>&mdash; The Octave Developers, May 28, 2015</em></small>
</p>
<h2>Community News Window in Octave 3.8</h2>
<p>
Beginning with the 3.8.x release series of Octave, we will be
displaying news about Octave community events here.  In Octave's GUI
interface, this window will appear when there is new information.
Octave will check for it at most once per day.
</p>
<p>
<small><em>&mdash; The Octave Developers, December 4, 2013</em></small>
</p>
